        "title": "Why I chose the 11\" over the 13\"",
        "body": "<p>I brought my current macbook over four years ago. It&rsquo;s still very usable but things are starting to get a bit laggy. The hardware is getting warn and compared to the models that are out these days it feels like dinosaur. I made a little extra money this year so started looking at my options. Apple&rsquo;s Macbooks were reved a few times over the year and I was zeroing in on the Macbook Air. I waited a few weeks made my final decision. </p>\n\n<p>I&rsquo;ve own a 13&quot; computer since I was in college and haven&rsquo;t looked back. The size is perfect for mobile computing and frankly I&rsquo;ve never needed anything more. I also own an external monitor in my office for doing any sort of work that requires that kind of screen real estate. When black Friday rolled around this year Apple was offering $100 off select machines so I ordered up a 13&quot; Macbook Air to be delivered the following week. </p>\n\n<p class=\"flickrpic\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/8270483397/\" title=\"Macbook. by joefearnley, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8082/8270483397_dcb6d2edd9.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" alt=\"Macbook.\"/></a></p>\n\n<p>When it arrived I opened the box and immediately notice how big it was. One of the reasons I wanted a Macbook Air is because of the mobility factor. I wanted something I could just throw in my bag or grab in a pinch and roll. Most of my computer use these days (<a href=\"http://blog.joefearnley.com/post/33363247380/holy-shit-im-a-dad\">since Zig was born</a>) is on the couch constantly closing it to attend to the little one or bagging it while going out of town. I found the 13&quot; to just be a little too big. </p>\n\n<p>I immediately started thinking about the 11&quot; version. If I got the version I wanted it would be pretty much the same machine at the 13&quot;, the main difference being the screen size. I headed to Best Buy to see the 11&quot; in action. It&rsquo;s difficult because I am not able to use it in my everyday life and being next to the 13&quot; it is really easy to see the screen size difference. The 13&quot; is much more appealing in the situation. </p>\n\n<p class=\"flickrpic\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/8271555986/\" title=\"macbook air by joefearnley, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8061/8271555986_bdb967f3d8.jpg\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" alt=\"macbook air\"/></a></p>\n\n<p>Another factor that came into play was Mountain Lion&rsquo;s full-screen mode. I find myself using all the time with the 13&quot; which is kind of a waste of space. The 11&quot; complements this perfectly and if I can live the screen size (which I have with the netbook I bought earlier in the year and was find with) I think this should have been the machine I purchased. I also thought about maybe picking up an iPad for couch and mobile usage but I learned I could not live without a physical keyboard the ones the docks offer aren&rsquo;t comparable to Apple&rsquo;s. The last factor for me was that the 11&quot; keyboard being the exact same size as the 13&quot;. One of the things I hated about the netbook was the keyboard was totally unusable for me. I was sold. </p>",
