        "title": "Holy Shit. I'm a Dad.",
        "body": "<p><figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"375\" data-orig-width=\"500\"><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/78008d62949e0845465625b3f11e32e6/6b94687b4c1893bf-28/s540x810/301569afc385fc9dd0ab74281f53b5a6ee9b5863.jpg\" data-orig-height=\"375\" data-orig-width=\"500\"/></figure></p>\n\n<p>I think it&rsquo;s time to review my bucket list. Who am I kidding? I don&rsquo;t have a bucket list. If I did I am sure it would change every year.  Regardless, having a child would not be near the top&hellip;not even close. Fortunately (or unfortunately, depending on how you look at it) I married a woman who&rsquo;s number 1 (or maybe 2) goal in life was to be a mother (or maybe that is what it has felt like in the last couple of years). We decided near the beginning of the year to try and have a child. Well, not only did the conception happen faster than I thought it would, but the last 9 to 10 months have flown right by and after a week, here I am, still standing, trying to be a dad. </p>\n\n<p>If there is one thing I have take away from this last week it&rsquo;s that being a dad really isn&rsquo;t that hard. It&rsquo;s more about just getting in there and giving it your best. My biggest fear going into this wasn&rsquo;t that I would do a bad job but how much personal time would be spent taking care of another human as opposed to do what ever I wanted. It still is. Since I have been married my &ldquo;do whatever I want&rdquo; time has dwindled little but raising a child is a whole new level. It&rsquo;s not about me anymore. My time is becoming more and more precious. I&rsquo;m about to be living and dying by the calendar. That&rsquo;s alright by me though. </p>\n\n<p>I realize my life has changed forever. Ever decision I make will (or at least should) take this little dude into consideration. I have a lot to learn and it&rsquo;s exciting. There will be many ups and many downs but we&rsquo;ll be alright. Right?</p>",
