        "title": "Happy Black History Month",
        "body": "<p>Born Robert Diggs the RZA is probably known best for being a member of the hip hop group The Wu-Tang Clan. Aside from Method Man he&rsquo;s probably had the most successful career as far as the other members of Wu-Tang go. From the solo work that he did to the Kill Bill stuff to now acting in a lead role on Californication I question what this man can&rsquo;t do.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"420\" data-orig-width=\"420\"><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/7bdb698de99302b98c33572767f793ab/796d7b6c92446893-4f/s540x810/e4ad522e236bb207f1cb293b78f61d912149b9f0.jpg\" data-orig-height=\"420\" data-orig-width=\"420\"/></figure></p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s obvious he was the mastermind behind Wu-Tang and I really got into them when I was in high school. Unfortunately I wasn&rsquo;t (and still not am) a big fan of their first record: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enter_the_Wu-Tang_(36_Chambers)\">Enter the Wu-Tang Clan</a>. It certainly had a rawness to it but by the time I got around to listening to it, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wu-Tang_Forever\">Wu-Tang Forever</a> was already out and that record completely blew my mind. After hearing <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=isumZjs3dKA\">Triumph</a> for the first time I was hooked. I went out and bought all of the solo records from each member. It was so different from not only what was on the radio but different from anything I had heard as far as hip hop was concerned. </p>\n\n<p>I also got into the first Gravediggaz record for a while. I was&rsquo;t crazy about the record but some of the verses and songs that RZA did were pretty awesome. Then <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bobby_Digital_in_Stereo\">Bobby Digital</a> dropped. I can&rsquo;t say that it was my favorite Wu-Tang solo record (that goes to Ghostface&rsquo;s Ironman) but it was something just kind of out there. So original and so good at the same time. Unfortunately after high school I kind of stopped listening to much hip hop but lately I&rsquo;ve been pulling old records out and giving them a spin, Bobby Digital included. I guess that&rsquo;s just one of the great thing about music. </p>\n\n<p>Happy Black History Month everyone. I&rsquo;m off to purchase a Wu-Tang Tshirt. </p>",
