                "content_raw": "<p>A little update on life. First things first…I am in the process of officially launching my pizza blog, <a href=\"http://joeymarinara.com/\">Joey Marinara</a>. It basically started out as a joke but after buying the domain name two years ago and a year after that actually starting to document things, I finally have a year’s worth of entries posted. I don’t really know if anything is going to happen with this blog but it’s kind of fun to do and who knows maybe it will attract some attention. Maybe even score a pie from it!\n\n<p>It’s abnormally cold for Michigan in mid to late April. It actually snowed two days in a row this past weekend. I remember when I graduated from college, that night we had a party and it snowed all night. As far as I’m concerned all bets are off until May. </p>\n\n<p>It was also record store day last Saturday. It’s kind of sad I actually have a record store a few blocks from my house that sells a bunch of vinyl and I’ve only been there two times this year. I used to have a plan to build this massive vinyl collection a few years ago. I soon realized how bad of an idea that is. Not that I don’t enjoy buying records (I can’t leave one of these stores without at least a couple) but that fact that if I were to ever move I would probably end up giving away most of them anyway. Regardless, I scored three record for 5 bucks including this bad boy:</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/5625744820/\" title=\"My vote for worst record cover ever. #recoredstoreday by joefearnley, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5189/5625744820_fb16c27d81.jpg\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" alt=\"My vote for worst record cover ever. #recoredstoreday\"></a></p>\n\n<p>What else has been going on in my life? Oh yeah, I’ve been keeping plenty busy playing music. I have band practice two times a week and both <a href=\"http://clydesdalescale.com/\">The Clydesdale Scale</a> and <a href=\"http://protectedleft.org\">Protected Left</a> have started playing shows. E.P.s for both band should be out soon. Vocals need to be finished for the Scale and mastering is in the works for PL. There is also a plan to do a mini tour next month. I’ll have to document that process.</p>\n\n<p>As for hacking is concerned. I just re-upped my Blue Host hosting account for another three months. After that I plan to move to a cheaper solution. In the process I have been looking at ways to somewhat modify some of my simpler websites I have out there. I’ve been playing around with things like Html5 and nodejs. So much to learn so little time.</p>\n\n<p>I did enter a contract with my gym. I’m going to have to save that lack of progress for different entry.</p></p>",
                "content": "<p>A little update on life. First things first&hellip;I am in the process of officially launching my pizza blog, <a href=\"http://joeymarinara.com/\">Joey Marinara</a>. It basically started out as a joke but after buying the domain name two years ago and a year after that actually starting to document things, I finally have a year&rsquo;s worth of entries posted. I don&rsquo;t really know if anything is going to happen with this blog but it&rsquo;s kind of fun to do and who knows maybe it will attract some attention. Maybe even score a pie from it!\n\n</p><p>It&rsquo;s abnormally cold for Michigan in mid to late April. It actually snowed two days in a row this past weekend. I remember when I graduated from college, that night we had a party and it snowed all night. As far as I&rsquo;m concerned all bets are off until May. </p>\n\n<p>It was also record store day last Saturday. It&rsquo;s kind of sad I actually have a record store a few blocks from my house that sells a bunch of vinyl and I&rsquo;ve only been there two times this year. I used to have a plan to build this massive vinyl collection a few years ago. I soon realized how bad of an idea that is. Not that I don&rsquo;t enjoy buying records (I can&rsquo;t leave one of these stores without at least a couple) but that fact that if I were to ever move I would probably end up giving away most of them anyway. Regardless, I scored three record for 5 bucks including this bad boy:</p>\n\n<p><div class=\"external-image-wrapper\" data-loading-text=\"Loading...\" data-src=\"http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5189/5625744820_fb16c27d81.jpg\">External image</div></p>\n\n<p>What else has been going on in my life? Oh yeah, I&rsquo;ve been keeping plenty busy playing music. I have band practice two times a week and both <a href=\"http://clydesdalescale.com/\">The Clydesdale Scale</a> and <a href=\"http://protectedleft.org\">Protected Left</a> have started playing shows. E.P.s for both band should be out soon. Vocals need to be finished for the Scale and mastering is in the works for PL. There is also a plan to do a mini tour next month. I&rsquo;ll have to document that process.</p>\n\n<p>As for hacking is concerned. I just re-upped my Blue Host hosting account for another three months. After that I plan to move to a cheaper solution. In the process I have been looking at ways to somewhat modify some of my simpler websites I have out there. I&rsquo;ve been playing around with things like Html5 and nodejs. So much to learn so little time.</p>\n\n<p>I did enter a contract with my gym. I&rsquo;m going to have to save that lack of progress for different entry.</p>",
