        "title": "Happy Black History Month",
        "body": "<p>This year for Black History Month, I honor none other than the great Chuck Berry. I grew up listening to a lot of Rock &lsquo;n Roll from the fifties that my parents would put on for parties or family road trips. Of course it included plenty of Mr. Berry including songs like <em>Maybellene</em> and <em>Roll Over Beethoven.</em></p>\n<p><em><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lhczdjvIX81qz98xr.jpg\"/></em></p>\n<p>No other song like <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johnny_B._Goode\">Johnny B. Goode</a>. Not only did I hear this song a ton of times around my house on Time Life greatest hits cassettes (and many more after discovering my parents record collection) but the scene from Back to the Future pretty much made me want to play the guitar. I mean look at <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johnny_B._Goode\">how many times this songs has been covered</a>, on the record, by history&rsquo;s most popular bands. Even Judas Preist for christ sakes. Now I know he&rsquo;s been to prison and apparently got busted for cocaine possession where they also found tapes women in his bathroom but you just can&rsquo;t deny the legacy he has left on the Rock 'n Roll world. He still tours and apparently passed out before a show in Chicago a couple of months of go.</p>\n<p>Happy Black History Month, Chuck!</p>",
