        "note_count": 0,
        "title": "2010 - a year in music (better late than never)",
        "body": "<p>It&rsquo;s that time of year again (well, sort of, only two months late) where I make two blog entries. One about the year in review and my hopes for the year to come and one about some of my favorite music of the year. This one&rsquo;s about music. So here goes, in no particular order, the jams I&rsquo;ve was rockin&rsquo; to in 2010:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>RVIVR</strong> - <strong><em>LP </em></strong><em>- </em>I dug The Shorebirds but I really feel like RVIVR is the sound that I was looking for when Latterman ended. And I&rsquo;m a sucker for a chick singer so that really put it over the top. They also released another E.P. before the year ended which was also very good.</li>\n<li><strong>Smoke or Fire </strong>-<strong> <em>The Speakeasy</em></strong> - I anticipated this record for the last couple of years. It was released on a day I had to rake leaves so i bought it to listen to while I do so and was instantly tuned in as soon as the first song started. It will always remind me of that smell of autumn.</li>\n<li><strong>The Riot Before </strong>- <strong>Rebellion </strong>&mdash; I first this band about three years ago after downloading an E.P. from Quote Unquote. This entire record is great. The last song is the most epic thing I&rsquo;ve heard in a while. </li>\n<li><strong>Iron Chic</strong> - <em><strong>Not Like This</strong></em> - I loved the demo these guys put out a couple years ago and have been waiting for a full length ever since. <em>Shitty Rambo</em> was OK in my book and I know there was more to this band. This record definitely showed that. </li>\n<li><strong>None More Black</strong> - <strong><em>Icons </em></strong>- This year was like 2005 all over again. I tought these guys were done for but they got back together and put out this monster of record. New drummer, same catchy, unique music. I just really hope they tour through the midwest this year.</li>\n<li><strong>GhostFace Killah</strong> - <em><strong>Apollo Kids</strong></em> - I haven&rsquo;t paid much attention to Ghostface (or hip-hop in general) in several years. I started to follow him on twitter earlier in the year and got to hear some of the songs early on. So I thought I would take a shot at this record and was presently surprised.  </li>\n<li><strong>Banquets</strong> - <em><strong>This is Our Concern, Dude</strong></em> - This was a short E.P. from the old singer of Let Me Run&rsquo;s new band. I can&rsquo;t pass up free music so I downloaded this record and it was great. The songs could easily been on Meet Me at the Bottom. I am excited to see what these guys do in 2011.</li>\n<li><strong>Coffee Project</strong> - <em><strong>Moved On</strong></em> - I got hooked on Coffee Project after hearing a couple of songs from a Paper + Plastic compilation released during 2009 some time. This dude writes some awesome tunes. Combined that with a trombone and its magic. </li>\n<li><strong>Brenden Kelly/Joe McMahon</strong> - <strong><em>Wasted Potential</em></strong> - I didn&rsquo;t actually listen to this record until I went on my cruise at the first of the year. Listening to this record while laying in the sun drinking a beer was damn near heaven, especially McMahon&rsquo;s side. I never thought the acoustic version of Smoke or Fire would be so awesome. I actually had never heard anything prior to Above this City from them and after listening to Beauty fades about fifty times over the week I had to seek out Worker&rsquo;s Union. </li>\n</ul><p>Honorable Mention</p>\n<ul><li><strong>No Trigger</strong> - <strong><em>Be Honest</em></strong> - I really beilieve canyoneer is one of the best records realeased in the 2000&rsquo;s so I have been anticipating something from these guys for a long time. It was only two songs though. I am REALLY looking forward to the full length this year.</li>\n<li><strong>Against Me!</strong> - <strong><em>White Crosses</em></strong> - I listened to this record a lot over easter weekend. But then I didn&rsquo;t really have the desire to go back to it. I was really good but for some reason very forgetful at the same time. </li>\n<li><strong>The Flatliners </strong>- <strong><em>Cavalcade</em></strong> - Everyone thought this record was so great. I don&rsquo;t know, for me, it left a lot to be desired. I thought The Great Awake was so much better. Maybe I should revisit it. </li>\n</ul>",
