        "note_count": 0,
        "title": "sunday social #50 - 2011 begins",
        "body": "<p>Well, 2010 came and went and frankly, I didn&rsquo;t accomplish as much as I would have liked to. I actually joined a gym, recorded some music, joined second band, started playing hockey again, and finished the wing challenge. I didn't actually lose any weight, lyrics still need to be finished (and recorded) for Rumfield&rsquo;s first EP (still haven&rsquo;t played a show either), and I got little done as far as programming is concerned. </p>\n<p>I plan for 2011 to be a better year. Here are some of the things I want to get accomplished:</p>\n<ul><li>Lose some weight and get into shape. I think everyone slightly over weight puts this on their list but it&rsquo;s something that needs to happen. </li>\n<li>Launch <a title=\"Joey Marinara\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://joeymarinara.com\">joeymarinara.com</a>. I&rsquo;ve been planning the direction for this site, much of it is in place, I just need to take the time to get it up and going.</li>\n<li>Learn node.js. A small app or site that utilizes this library.</li>\n<li>Create a django project. Another fail of last year&rsquo;s goals that I started, but soon ran out of time to complete it.</li>\n<li>Put out some more <a title=\"The Browncast\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://thebrowncast.com\">browncast</a> episodes. We began this, some things went down, and now we need to continue.</li>\n<li>Get some more tattoos. </li>\n<li>Blog more. I don't necessarily need to write more, maybe just some more technical-related posts and share my life a little bit more.</li>\n<li>Read more. Something I&rsquo;ve been need to do a lot more lately.</li>\n</ul><p>I think that&rsquo;s about it. This year began with a week of vacation to the Caribbean. Not exactly the way I would like it to start out but hell, you have to start some where.</p>",
        "reblog": {
            "comment": "<p>Well, 2010 came and went and frankly, I didn’t accomplish as much as I would have liked to. I actually joined a gym, recorded some music, joined second band, started playing hockey again, and finished the wing challenge. I didn't actually lose any weight, lyrics still need to be finished (and recorded) for Rumfield’s first EP (still haven’t played a show either), and I got little done as far as programming is concerned. </p>\n<p>I plan for 2011 to be a better year. Here are some of the things I want to get accomplished:</p>\n<ul><li>Lose some weight and get into shape. I think everyone slightly over weight puts this on their list but it’s something that needs to happen. </li>\n<li>Launch <a title=\"Joey Marinara\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://joeymarinara.com\">joeymarinara.com</a>. I’ve been planning the direction for this site, much of it is in place, I just need to take the time to get it up and going.</li>\n<li>Learn node.js. A small app or site that utilizes this library.</li>\n<li>Create a django project. Another fail of last year’s goals that I started, but soon ran out of time to complete it.</li>\n<li>Put out some more <a title=\"The Browncast\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://thebrowncast.com\">browncast</a> episodes. We began this, some things went down, and now we need to continue.</li>\n<li>Get some more tattoos. </li>\n<li>Blog more. I don't necessarily need to write more, maybe just some more technical-related posts and share my life a little bit more.</li>\n<li>Read more. Something I’ve been need to do a lot more lately.</li>\n</ul><p>I think that’s about it. This year began with a week of vacation to the Caribbean. Not exactly the way I would like it to start out but hell, you have to start some where.</p>",
            "tree_html": ""
        },
