        "title": "Ride this bitch to hell",
        "body": "<p>So this morning Strung Out came on my iPod on accident and the song was <i>Her Name in Blood</i>. For a moment it really took me back. As all music does, really, to that moment in your life in which listened to that record (in my case often repeatedly). For <i>Exile in Oblivion</i>, it was the fall of 2004. Life for me wasn&rsquo;t the best it could be. I was stressed out about school, was working a job a 12 year old could do, and my love life was in shambles. Then this record came out and I found myself immersed in it. I would listen to it constantly on my way to school and back and would blast it all weekend. </p>\n\n<p>I remember the day it came out, Jason and I went to three stores in search for it. The funny thing is none of the independent stores had it, we found it at a Circuit City of all places. Anyway, we picked up some forties, went home and played this thing all night. It was a Tuesday and we didn&rsquo;t have a care in the world. We called it the listening party. Just us two and some weird dude that randomly knocked on our back door looking for something that escapes me at the moment while our room mates came home wondering what the hell was going on. </p>\n\n<p>We got to see strung out play a month later. It would be the first of many to come but it was just the fact that it was the first and I had been a fan for years. </p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s funny, every time news gets posted about strung out on punknews, some jerk always comments about the lyric &ldquo;give it away, give it away, ride this bitch to he&rsquo;ll&rdquo; saying how horrible it is. I don&rsquo;t think it&rsquo;s that bad and in the context of the song pretty good. Hearing this song once again kind of brings it all back. </p>\n\n<div>\n<object width=\"425\" height=\"344\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/oaenlldZOso?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US\"><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/oaenlldZOso?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\"></embed></object>\n</div>",
