        "title": "gitin' a hold on things",
        "body": "<p>Almost three years ago I I switched my blog from a custom engine I wrote to <a href=\"http://wordpress.org\">Wordpress</a>. Things have changed and an attempt to move away from paid hosting I am moving my blog to <a href=\"http://tumblr.com\">Tumblr</a>. I&rsquo;ve always thought it was a good platform to not only write entries but to post random things I come across on the internet. I wanted to preserve what I could as far as historic entries were concerned so I wrote <a href=\"http://github.com/joefearnley/php-wp2tumblr\">a script</a> that read in my Wordpress export and posted all entries to Tumblr. I have a lot of options out there as far as blogging services go so if I get fed up with Tumblr I can always move somewhere else.</p>\n\n<p>I also revamp <a href=\"http://joefearnley.com\">joefearnley.com</a>, making more of a &ldquo;personal landing page&rdquo; (lamest name in the world). I didn&rsquo;t mean to take a page from services like <a href=\"http://about.me\">about.me</a> or <a href=\"http://flavors.me/\">flavors.me</a> but noticed them soon after I created my own. The neat thing is I am utilizing <a href=\"http://pages.github.com/\">github&rsquo;s pages</a> to <a href=\"http://github.com/joefearnley/joefearnley.github.com\">host it</a>. Moving further from paying for web hosting. <strike>Apparently custom domains with github pages is a paid-only offerring. So I guess I&rsquo;ll be using my blue host account for a little longer. </strike> (Apparently, I&rsquo;m an idiot - <a href=\"http://support.github.com/discussions/email/13401-contact-custom-domain-name?anon_token=17976b8b0c0e6d8dfe709f18107a80b188921b99\">see here</a>).</p>\n\n<p>For the future? Well I will continuing blogging about the current haps in my life and my thoughts on specific current events. I&rsquo;d also like to post more about music I am currently into as well new discoveries in the software world. I&rsquo;ve also always wanted to review <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blaxploitation\">black exploitation</a> films since I started doing this blog five years ago, but that may have to wait until next year.</p>",
