        "title": "sunday social #49 - strung out on Strung Out",
        "body": "<p>These last four days have been a whirlwind. On Wednesday I won some tickets to see Strung Out play a taping of <a href=\"http://www.jbtvonline.com/\">JBTV</a>. There was something surreal about the whole situation. I&rsquo;ve been listening to this band for something like fifteen years, have seen them live about four times, and it&rsquo;s safe to say they are my favorite band. To see them play in front of me with nine other people was so awesome yet so strange. It seems like everyone else is over this band but I still think they fucking rule.\n\n</p><div style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/5027671699/\" title=\"Strung out at jbtv by joefearnley, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4085/5027671699_ee27c8f637.jpg\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" alt=\"Strung out at jbtv\"/></a>\n</div>\n\nAfter a few beers and a game of Jeopardy at the L&amp;L (which comes on at 3:30 in Chicago or at least that day it did) Jason and I met up with Steve. After another beer at his apartment we headed downtown on the train to Reggies. It was a rad show. The first band we saw was <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/wearetheunion\">We are the Union</a>. They reminded me of a young Less than Jake. Very catchy with unnecessary trombone and a guitar player that was trying way too hard. Next to play was <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/mutepunkrock\">Mute</a> who absolutely killed it. Very Canadian (French), very punk, but that kind of skate punk that everyone thought died in the 90&rsquo;s. It was surprising, but a good surprise. <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rufio\">Rufio</a> played next. I kind of fell out of touch with this band after their first record. They were certainly good though. I just could never get into the singer&rsquo;s voice. Finally Strung Out played. It was rad, like always, even seeing them hours before. \n\nThe next day Jason and I hit Wrigleyville for a Cubs game. Of course we had to make a pit stop at <a href=\"http://www.luckysandwich.com/\">Lucky&rsquo;s</a> to grab some lunch. We got the capicola sandwich which was amazing. When we got to the stadium I was quite surprised at how small it was. There were only a handful of bad seats in the house. Regardless, the Cubs got smoked and we had to head back to Michigan. Wish we could have stayed for longer.\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/5020562599/\" title=\"Tons of fun. by joefearnley, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4147/5020562599_a7e0307fa4.jpg\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" alt=\"Tons of fun.\"/></a>\n</div>\n\nThe funniest part was when we were walking out of the stadium we saw a guy with a <a href=\"http://carlthejanitor.com/racki-from-youngblood/\">Carl Racki</a> jersey. A great way to top off a good couple of days.",
