        "title": "sunday social #42 – northern michigan 2.1",
        "body": "<p>Huh, my first sunday social post in a while. The last one was about my last trip to northern Michigan. Maybe a coincidence, maybe not. Onward. \n\nSo this past weekend we took yet another trek to the great city of Bear Lake. Unfortunately, the weather gods fought us tooth and nail the entire weekend. No sunny days, no tubing on the lake, not even a boat ride during the day. I guess you can&rsquo;t win them all. Don&rsquo;t get me wrong, the weekend didn&rsquo;t go with out its moments. We had two Bear Lake virgins join us which made things quite exciting. I could go into more detail with this, but I don&rsquo;t want to get anyone in trouble. One new thing to me was cooking hotdogs wrapped in bacon. Great for the heart, I&rsquo; told&hellip;.\n\n</p><div style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/3846654145/\" title=\"Bacon dogs by joefearnley, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3465/3846654145_32210a01ab.jpg\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" alt=\"Bacon dogs\"/></a>\n</div>\n\nThe weekend after next, I&rsquo;m going to Chicago. In my eyes, labor day basically bring this summer to a close. Looking back, I did not lose any weight nor did I learn python. This brings up another issue all together. I actually started to learn it, but things began to get in the way. Life, really, but it made me begin to thing about learning a new language or push myself to learn more about the ones I already &ldquo;know&rdquo;. I&rsquo;ve been thinking more about simplifying my life more altogether. Maybe learn ruby? Who knows.\n\nI wouldn&rsquo;t say it went completely unproductive. I managed to squeeze in a new band or two that have yet to write six songs. And I grew a lot of grass. I wish I had some pictures to show the before and after of my yard. The old man would be impressed. I got two weeks, left, let&rsquo;s make something happen.",
