        "title": "conclusions, conclusions...",
        "body": "<p>I came to the conclusion last week that <a title=\"http://joef.org/2009/05/16/apparently-it-isnt-2007-anymore/\" href=\"http://joef.org/2009/05/16/apparently-it-isnt-2007-anymore/\">its not 2007 anymore</a>, but in fact, its 2009. Summer is right a round the corner. Over the last week, I had some vacation, rachel turned a quarter of a century, and the red wings clinched the western conference. As the summer begins, I feel I need to set some goals.</p>\n\n<p>One of my goals is to learn a new programming language. I first thought I would take a stab at a bunch of them, but the way I poke at things it would probably be meaningless. Plus I don&rsquo;t want to be an inch deep and a mile wide. At this point it&rsquo;s a toss up between python and objective-C. I&rsquo;ve made a hello world app with both, and after more research, python would probably be the faster one to get my head around. One is compiled, one is interpreted. This brings another dimension to it, but that&rsquo;s not one really worth getting into here. Basically one would be for developing iphone applications, the other for furthering my web development skills. Decisions, decisions.</p>\n\n<p>Another goal is to make some progress musically. I have a couple things in the works and have confidence something will work. It&rsquo;s simply a matter of applying myself.</p>\n\n<p>The third is to get into some better physical shape. How I am going to do this with working, learning a new language, playing music, and being at rachel&rsquo;s beck and call, who knows? Time management and a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Getting_Things_Done\">gtd</a> schedule maybe?I got audio books and a commute. Come on and convince me.</p>",
