        "title": "sunday social #36 - rise from your grave",
        "body": "<p>OK. Some weekends seem to last longer than others. This past weekend was no exception. In the short sense.</p>\n\n<p>OK, the jokes up, I got nothing to write about. I haven&rsquo;t had much to write about in the last two weeks. There is only so much I can talk shit about how effed up the current state of music is or how much I try to be ahead of the curve in the tech world. Talk about a mile wide.</p>\n\n<p>Next weekend I am heading home for easter. I&rsquo;m not a religious man, but I think the time I am going to spend with my family is long over due. Thinking back, I haven&rsquo;t been home since x-mas time. Its a little strange these days. The old man and I will hopefully get to play some golf.</p>\n\n<p>Its amazing how much family time goes from conversation to lets pay attention to the children in the room. Ultimately, that&rsquo;s what it&rsquo;s come down to. I&rsquo;m fine with that because really, there is only so much you can hear the same stories over and over. And in Dan&rsquo;s case, bad jokes. Again, I am very clueless when it comes to JC mysteriously rising from being dead and we celebrate it buy eating and drinking. I think the story goes goes. Someone correct me if I got it wrong. In the meantime I will be looking into new topics to write about.</p>",
