                "content_raw": "<p>I read <a title=\"http://www.altpress.com/specials/blog/mike/2009/03/why-is-it.cfm\" href=\"http://www.altpress.com/specials/blog/mike/2009/03/why-is-it.cfm\">this blog entry</a> today and wanted to comment on it but had way too much to say so I decided to make a post about it.</p>\n\n<p>The question is - Why is it? Well for starters, any kid can get on the internet right now and download the entire angels an airwaves discography for free in a couple minutes. Wait, I am pretty sure Tom Delonge is rich. Bad example.</p>\n\n<p>Any kid can download virtually any music they want in a matter of minutes because of the internet. If this technology was available twenty years ago, they same thing would have happened. The price of music is total shit these days and that’s a result of many things, not just kids downloading music illegally. I’m thinking more and more people starting bands these days are realizing that that won’t make a ton of money let alone a living off it.</p>\n\n<p>Don’t start a band these days expecting to be the next led zepplin because that’s never going to happen. You may get that big, but you’ll never afford your own jet before the label takes its cut. Why do you think every rapper (and for that matter, every punk rocker) these days are starting their own clothing line? They have been for years. They saw this shit coming, why can’t everyone else? Partly, I think its because when 12-year-old kids see a band on MTV2, they immediately think they are rich. Didn’t TLC or MC Hammer teach us anything? I guess if you are 12, then you probably have no idea who these people are anyway.</p>\n\n<p>Being that bands only play for like a half an hour every night, it seems to me that they really don’t deserve to make a living off of it anyway.  What other job has these kind of hours and the perks that come along with it? Shut up and play your guitar, drink your free drinks and meet new chicks in different towns each night. I don’t feel sorry for you. I also question why a magazine that has access to every label in the country asks a questions like this. Shit, they’re lucky they can afford to print anything, so I guess its because their means of making a living depend on it.</p>\n\n<p>Get with the times man. I don’t want you on my ebook reader.</p>",
