        "title": "going green",
        "body": "<p>If the world ends in 200 years because of my contribution to the demise of our environment, would I really feel that bad? Do I feel bad now? Not really. If I wipe my ass with recycled toilet paper, only my ass feels the pain. I&rsquo;d kind of like to know if I am going to live forever. Can I suck some blood and cross my fingers? I, for one, am personally sick of questions about the future.\n\nIf anything is going green in this world today, its the the clothing of americans on st. paddy&rsquo;s day. I only own one green shirt and it was exhausted by the time this mourning rolled around. Blue green worked though&hellip;well maybe just for <a title=\"http://jc1701.com/otho.html\" href=\"http://jc1701.com/otho.html\">Otho</a>. For what its worth, I drank this, ate a hamburger and watched the family guy.\n</p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"IMAGE_603 by joefearnley, on Flickr\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/3363667433/\"><img src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3537/3363667433_b9e1fa1559.jpg\" alt=\"IMAGE_603\" width=\"400\" height=\"500\"/></a></div>\nWhere does the time go? Happy st. paddy&rsquo;s day.",
