        "title": "sunday social #34 - a guided tour of chicago",
        "body": "This past weekend was spent in the windy city of Chicago. Damn dude, seriously? We had a lot of fun. The weekend started off with a stop by <a title=\"http://www.rydaly.com/\" href=\"http://www.rydaly.com/\">ry guys</a> with a warm up of carlsbad and the beamer. He lives near the actual logan square which apparently consists of a lot of hispanic patrons. Who knew?\n\nAfter an arguable stretch through the many streets that looked exactly the same, we finally made it to <a title=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boystown,_Chicago\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boystown,_Chicago\">boys town</a>. With no parking spot. Let me know the next time you can luck out as well as I did. Once all was said and done (and a trip to the &lsquo;bay where I saw joe thunderbird. Small world, ehh?), it was back to steve&rsquo;s apartment for chicago-style pizza and a review of blazing saddles. Break&rsquo;s over boys.\n\nSaturday was different story. Actually quite the same. A little car trouble, but nothing that wasn&rsquo;t handled correctly. B. roskowski was getting married and the party ensued. A tranny said dave looked like candy at a store we stopped at. Where was I going with this? Oh yeah, the tequillla bar, where dave was presented with a $200 dollar dinner bill while steve got his bromance on. It was cute though.\n\nAfter another bar and spilled tecate, it was back to steve&rsquo;s apartment. Then, my friends, it was off the the <a title=\"http://www.yelp.com/biz/l-and-l-tavern-chicago\" href=\"http://www.yelp.com/biz/l-and-l-tavern-chicago\">L and L</a>. Here, was had a Pabst and listened to some rock tunes. Hoping to see brenden kelly, the night did not go uneventful. The next stop was the wiener circle where I got chewed out by hotdog maker and told by a guy with a pony knob that if I kept up my attitude I would be biting the curb. Oh well, his loss. The whole thing was a little but like this. Only that it was St. Patty&rsquo;s day weekend and the first niced-weathered day of the year.\n<div style=\"text-align: center\"><object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\"><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"><param name=\"src\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/vo1LPf9mnyU&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1\"><embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/vo1LPf9mnyU&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed></object></div>\nThe night ended with a last beer at ricks and a cab ride home. Unfortunately, <a title=\"http://www.alsbeef.com/\" href=\"http://www.alsbeef.com/\">Al&rsquo;s italian beef</a> was closed on our way back to kalamazoo on wednesday, so no cheese stakes were had. Oh well, maybe next time.",
