        "title": "sunday social #32 - valentimes day",
        "body": "<p>Can I be honest for a moment? I fucking hate this time of year. The weather sucks, odds are you are slacking on your new years resolutions, and along comes the most ridiculous holiday of the year. I would give that to sweetest day, but I don&rsquo;t considered that shit even relevant. Frankly, I don&rsquo;t even know valentines days is considered a holiday.</p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s the same shit every year. I go to the store and stand around the card isle with the rest of the idiot males in the world, looking for a card that&rsquo;s supposed to be romantic, yet at the same time. Its so overrated and I feel absolutely forced to do it. What would be even more romantic is if you did this on another random day during the year. I have a feeling the significant other in the relationship would appreciate it more. Yet if you don&rsquo;t do anything on valentines day, odds are you are going to be in the doghouse for quote sometime, no matter how cynical the significant other can be.</p>\n\n<p>As for my valentines day this year, it was pretty laid back. I wasn&rsquo;t expected to make any great dinner plans nor was I expected to do anything out of the ordinary. I think I make it up on the rest of the year with lets say, I don&rsquo;t know, Christmas, birthdays, anniversaries, Easter, forth of July, Halloween&hellip;when does it stop? Never. It never stops. I gave up sweetest day a long time ago and don&rsquo;t plan to go back. Maybe, just maybe, if I can convince the rest of the world how ridiculous some of these traditional holidays are, I can start knocking a few more of they list.</p>",
