        "note_count": 0,
        "title": "AP + ET = match made somewhere?",
        "body": "I was listening to the latest a<a title=\"http://www.altpress.com/podcast/\" href=\"http://www.altpress.com/podcast/\">lternative press podcast</a> when I noticed something that I haven&rsquo;t heard in one of these in the last two years of listening to them. In the beginning, middle and the end there was a big fat advertisement for <a title=\"http://www.epitaph.com/\" href=\"http://www.epitaph.com/\">epitaph records</a>. I suppose the magazine business is a dying industry, so you have to make money where you can and yet <a title=\"http://www.altpress.com/specials/blog/mike/2008/11/easy-way-out.html\" href=\"http://www.altpress.com/specials/blog/mike/2008/11/easy-way-out.html\">not sell out</a>. Later that day while following <a title=\"http://twitter.com/joefearnley\" href=\"http://twitter.com/joefearnley\">my twitter feed</a> as normal, I noticed that AP released <a title=\"http://www.altpress.com/apmag/248.htm\" href=\"http://www.altpress.com/apmag/248.htm\">who was going to be on the cover of the upcoming months edition</a>. Lone behold, <a title=\"http://www.myspace.com/thursday\" href=\"http://www.myspace.com/thursday\">its two</a> <a title=\"http://www.myspace.com/bmth\" href=\"http://www.myspace.com/bmth\">Epitaph bands</a>. \n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://c4.ac-images.myspacecdn.com/images02/63/l_f1f16632ce1642dc9bc805e56d178253.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"284\" height=\"343\"/></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://c3.ac-images.myspacecdn.com/images02/39/l_c9005055ab7647288bf7b5ecc23690b2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"281\" height=\"340\"/></p>\n\nConincodence? Maybe. I just have a hard time getting over how elitest these editors act but turn around and write about some of the bands they do.",
