        "title": "sunday social #30 - 2008 re-cap",
        "body": "<p>After a couple of weeks off of the blog, I feel I have to reflect on another year in life gone past. 2008, like past years, was an interesting one. Really only a couple milestones in my life were passed. And when I say milestone, I say financial endeavors that I probably shouldn&rsquo;t have taken. Yet looking back, I really don&rsquo;t regret it.\n\nDuring the first part of the year, I purchased a house. It&rsquo;s probably one of the most unique ones I have encountered in my life. First thing was first, I built a bar in the basement and was on my way. I also purchased a new automobile. This was certainly needed and now I have an ipod adapter so my shit&rsquo;s going totally digital. A bit scary, but unevitable.\n\nAs far as resolutions go this year, I was a little behind once I crossed that line. I certainly did blog more, but excercise was about nill. I plan to turn this around in 2009. I want to consistainly keep up with the blog, but keeping up with a healthier lifestyle is higher up on the list. Tomorrow starts a new test of overall self control. Oh, and I want to get this rock and roll endevour moving in a faster direction. Looking back I had something in my hand that I let slip right through the tips because of laziness. This year, that&rsquo;s gotta change.\n\nSpeaking of music, I also compilied a list of my favorite listened to music of 2008. In no particular order.\n</p><ul>\n\t<li>Shorebirds - <em>Its Gonna Get Ugly</em></li>\n\t<li>The Gaslight Anthem - <em>The &lsquo;59 Sound</em> and <em>The Senor and the Queen</em></li>\n\t<li>Polar Bear Club - <em>Sometimes Things Just Disappear</em></li>\n\t<li>Smartbomb - <em>Chaos And Lawlessness</em></li>\n\t<li>Joey Cape - <em>Bridge</em></li>\n\t<li>Cheeky - <em>Choke On A Cheeseburger</em></li>\n\t<li>Dillinger Four - <em>CIVILWAR</em></li>\n\t<li>Dead to Me - <em>Little Brother</em></li>\n</ul>\nThe things to point out here is that I am totally predictable when it comes to music. There were other things I listened to a lot last year, but they were not released within the 365 days, so I feel like I cannot put them on this list.\n\nOne last thing to mention here is that I have started <a title=\"the browncast\" href=\"http://thebrowncast.joef.org/\">a podcast</a>. This is something that I didn&rsquo;t really plan on in 2008, but the ball is rolling and we plan to continue. 2009, here we come.",
