        "title": "sunday social #28 - christ its cold",
        "body": "<p>With x-mas coming up this thursday, life is not as hectic as one would think. I have all of my shopping done and I&rsquo;m ready for some days off of work in these next couple of weeks. It seems like thanksgiving was yesterday and I know this holiday season is just going to fly by. So we have to make that shit last.</p>\n\n<p>On top of the craziness of the season, its been the coldest week of the year so far. It sort of got up into the mid-twenties there for a couple of days, but today it was in the single digits. The only time I went outside was to shovel the driveway so I can get to work tomorrow mourning. So this lead me to spend the whole day on the couch working on <a title=\"http://thebrowncast.joef.org/\" href=\"http://thebrowncast.joef.org/\">the new design for the browncast</a>. I copped the design from <a title=\"http://www.copyblogger.com/\" href=\"http://www.copyblogger.com/\">copyblogger</a> because it was free. So I added the brown touch to it.</p>\n\n<p>A strange thing happened while I was working on updating the new theme I got a random twitter from <a title=\"http://www.blubrry.com/\" href=\"http://www.blubrry.com/\">bluberry </a>telling me they have a <a title=\"http://www.blubrry.com/powerpress/\" href=\"http://www.blubrry.com/powerpress/\">podcast plugin</a> for wordpress. Being that I couldn&rsquo;t get <a title=\"http://www.mightyseek.com/podpress/\" href=\"http://www.mightyseek.com/podpress/\">podpress</a> to work with this theme, I thought I would give it a whirl. And lone behold, it work. My only complaint is that it doesn&rsquo;t have the statistics that <a title=\"http://www.mightyseek.com/podpress/\" href=\"http://www.mightyseek.com/podpress/\">podpress</a> did, so I will have to look into this.</p>\n\n<p>So I guess its off the holidays. Merry x-mas.</p>",
