        "body": "These past couple of weeks have been a little wild and I have so much to write about. But I don&rsquo;t really feel like it. Nothing witty is coming into my mind regarding these events, so I&rsquo;m just gonna go for it.\n\nFirst things first. Dave graduated college last week and of course, we had to celebrate. It was the prefect opportunity for <a title=\"http://www.myspace.com/drinkthebrownout\" href=\"http://www.myspace.com/drinkthebrownout\">the brownout</a> to host another party. So we did. But being that its so close to the holidays, we decided to have a x-mas party as opposed to a boo-boo juice party. We kind of thought a boo-boo juice / malt liquor party would be better celebrated in the summer time.\n\nSo we forged on with the x-mas party. We went out and bought some ridiculous looking sweaters and a lot of lights. A giant santa was also purchased and it was required that you get <a title=\"http://24.247.123.70:8084/christmas_pics/christmas_pics.html\" href=\"http://24.247.123.70:8084/christmas_pics/christmas_pics.html\">your picture taken</a> next to it before you enter. Apparently santa really <a title=\"http://24.247.123.70:8084/christmas_pics/102_3555.JPG\" href=\"http://24.247.123.70:8084/christmas_pics/102_3555.JPG\">likes his rum</a>.\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"102_3566 by joefearnley, on Flickr\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/3116733647/\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3225/3116733647_9e42e95a89.jpg\" alt=\"102_3566\" width=\"404\" height=\"302\"/></a></p>\n\nSo for the next couple weeks I will be busy with the holidays. Once santa visits my home, I am hoping to have more gadgets to get way more media to this site and else where. Expect a lot of av whether it comes in the form of music, talk radio, or personal interviews.\n\nIn sadder news, Florence Procko passed away. You will be missed.\n\nAlso, <a title=\"http://browncast.joef.org/2008/12/browncast-002-sound-effects-and-sponsors/\" href=\"http://browncast.joef.org/2008/12/browncast-002-sound-effects-and-sponsors/\">the latest browncast</a> is up. Go and take a listen. Don&rsquo;t be afraid to let us know what you think.",
