        "title": "sunday social #28 - thankstaking",
        "body": "<p>Ah thanksgiving. This is always an interesting time of year. Its very similar to christmas, except without some of the magic. This year seemed to be unusually cold though. I ate a lot of food and drank my fair share. I saw plenty of people I haven&rsquo;t seen in a while, so that was nice. Yet its always a little uncomfortable to try and catch up with so many people at one time. I guess that&rsquo;s one of the reason&rsquo;s I keep this blog up to date. I&rsquo;m thinking about making a business card with just my website address on it. You know, for the next year or so.</p>\n\n<p>The work week was a short one and once back in Kalamazoo, I got some work done around my house. I scored a record player that works great along with a free <a title=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barry_Manilow_Live\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barry_Manilow_Live\">Barry Manilow double live album</a>. As soon as I got home yesterday, I played some <em><a title=\"on the dark side\" href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zgloaS4NGyM\">On the Dark Side</a></em> and rocked out for a while. It seemed everyone around me thought is was pretty ridiculous that I was purchasing vinyl records without something to play them on. But that&rsquo;s all changed now. So I guess you could say this wasn&rsquo;t much of a giving holiday.</p>\n\n<p>This year also had a good representation of west michigan high school football teams in the state finals. Of course the Mona Shores Sailors we not there, but being that I spent more than half of my K-12 education in the Muskegon Public School System, I felt somewhat personally represented.</p>\n\n<p>I haven&rsquo;t started my christmas shopping yet, so the next couple of weeks should be fun. I will be scouring the toy isles searching for the perfect toy for my nieces and nephews. My heart goes out to those who lost their life over deals at walmart.</p>",
