                "content_raw": "<p>Whewww….what a weekend. I spent it this time in the gold ole north michigan. Unlike the <a title=\"northern michigan\" href=\"http://joef.org/2008/08/19/sunday-social-17-northern-michigan/\">summer version</a>, this one was a little colder. Actually, it really didn’t get colder until friday night, but when it hit, it hit hard. But if there is one thing I learned this weekend, its when you’re down and out, your got to get right back up and continue the journey.\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"IMG_3260 by joefearnley, on Flickr\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/3017933936/\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3234/3017933936_bbee25b16f_m.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_3260\" width=\"240\" height=\"160\"></a></p>\nBecause the water was kind of out of the question, we had to make fun in other forms. We visited the local taverns, saw a house made out of bottles, and eventually backwards up gravity hill. I know, I know, its sounds a little strange, but the intensity was there. Even if no one else could feel it. I, for one, am a believer. Not necessarily in god, but in the waiters at crystal mountain. They were a joy and it was nice to meet someone up there that got the jokes and could follow suit.\n\nI don’t really know what I am talking about and I gotta hit the sack. Its late and my stomach needs recovering. Too much <a title=\"beer\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/3018004598/\">beer</a> and too much <a title=\"The bear\" href=\"http://www.classicrockthebear.com/\">bear</a>.</p>",
