        "title": "who do think I am?",
        "body": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\">I set a goal this week to write a blog entry everyday. Being that I will away from a computer for three days after tonight, I thought I would try to squeak one out. So with small amount of hope, here goes…</p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">I set a goal at the beginning of the year to make more blog posts. Now that the year is slowly winding down, I find myself trying to make up for the lost time I missed during most of the autumn of this year. I don&rsquo;t know if any of you have tried to consistently update a blog, but it’s a little difficult to do. Wait, let me re-phrase that, it’s difficult to consistently make blog posts that are opinionative on a certain subject, I suppose unless you have nothing to do all day. Then it would probably a snap. My problem is coming up with things to write about a few times a week without sounding like an idiot or posting you tube videos and making a smart ass remark about it. This is a simple way to get a post in, but doesn&rsquo;t take that much thought. Maybe I should start taking that route to fill in some of the gaps? Maybe I should make a new years resolution to only make posts like that?</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the reasons I wanted to create more posts this year was to get better at writing. As you can tell from pretty much this pass year, it’s probably declined if anything. I don&rsquo;t know how to form sentences correctly, I have a hard time disguising where to stop and start a paragraph, and my grammar is that of a 10th grade high school student. I guess I was hoping repetition would take hold and bring me to the next level. So much for that.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Regardless, I&rsquo;m gonna keep doing what I&rsquo;m doing. It seems to be working and to be honest no one really reads these posts anyway. Trust me, I read the metrics. The only time it ever goes up is when I create a post and have to revise it increasing my page views along the way.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For now, I&rsquo;m off to north part of the mitten. I&rsquo;ll be back on Sunday with a re cap of the weekend. See you then!</p>",
