        "title": "from sea to kind of dull sea",
        "body": "<p>Last night America took a turn for the better by electing Barack Obama. I guess it wasn&rsquo;t the fact that Obama himself got elected but that fact that George W. is no longer in office. And to see an African American to get elected president was probably one of the wildest things I&rsquo;ve ever seen. I honestly never thought this would happen in my lifetime and I&rsquo;m a quarter century in to this bad boy.</p>\n\n<p>Coming from a working class family where my dad was a plumber in the union and my mother a nurse at Planned Parenthood, its really difficult for me to shake my democratic roots. Yet, for the first time in my life, this past year has let me understand the republican side of things rather than brushing it off as bullshit. It might have something to do with actually paying attention to the political race which I have never done until this election. Who knows.</p>\n\n<p>Regardless of who got elected, either one of these candidates would have a hard time trying to clean up the mess of a country the US is right now. Good luck Barack, your gonna need it. Lets keep this ship on course.</p>",
