        "title": "myspace crossposting",
        "body": "<p><img src=\"./wp-content/themes/couch/images/myspace.png\" class=\"imbedded-image\"/><br/>\nDuring some randoms surfs last evening, I stumbled upon this. Its plug-in for wordpress that automatically posts blog entry to my <a title=\"http://www.myspace.com/joefearnley\" href=\"http://www.myspace.com/joefearnley\">myspace account</a> when I post and entry on this site. I have been looking for a plug-in with this functionality for quite some time. The only other thing I could find that was even close was a site that screen scraped <a title=\"joe fearnley myspace\" href=\"http://blog.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.ListAll&amp;friendID=12302469\">my myspace blog</a> and parsed it so I could post it here on <a title=\"joef.org\" href=\"http://joef.org\">joef.org</a>.</p>\n\n<p>I&rsquo;m thinking this might have something to due with Myspace&rsquo;s closed architecture. But <a title=\"http://code.google.com/apis/opensocial/\" href=\"http://code.google.com/apis/opensocial/\">a lot&rsquo;s happened</a> in the last couple years with api&rsquo;s showing up on these social networking sites. So this is either the beginning to something really cool, or it may not be working for much longer. For now, I have look in to hacking this sucker so the format isn&rsquo;t <a title=\"first cross post\" href=\"http://blog.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.view&amp;friendID=12302469&amp;blogID=446046689\">so ridiculous</a>.</p>",
