        "title": "sunday social #19 - in due time",
        "body": "<p>So this past weekend was an interesting one. No getting out of control, no crazies nights, just very relaxed. I went back to Muskegon on friday and stayed until sunday. I saw the family, played a little golf and did not go tubing. Instead I opted for band practice which was long over due with a drummer. At this point I don&rsquo;t think we will make the battle of the bands but the attempt for it was exactly what the band needed. We haven&rsquo;t practiced as full band yet and don&rsquo;t even have a name let alone a demo recorded. It OK, all in due time. I just like the fact the ball is finally beginning to roll on this one.</p>\n\n<p>The other thing that made this weekend interesting was that I stayed away from the alcohol. Honestly it was a little tough being labor day weekend. Even though it was the perfect day for it, I am somewhat glad I didn&rsquo;t go on that tube trip. The outcome probably wouldn&rsquo;t have been good. But for now, its back to the grind at work. Well, and home. I have to finish cutting down the tree in my front yard. Unfortunately, I only have a couple days off until the end of the year, so fun certainly awaits.</p>",
