        "body": "<p>Holy shit this pass week was something else. It was very jam packed and I don&rsquo;t know where to begin. First of all, I got my hands totally dirty with some very <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/2601154313/\" title=\"electrical work\">not-up-to code electrical work</a> in my basement. I installed five outlets, two lights, and one switch on two new separate breakers. Honestly it wasn&rsquo;t that difficult, only very scary installing a new circuit breaker. Knowing the amount of electricity that flows through that box, I couldn&rsquo;t help be very timid when the whole thing went down. The moment I turned the lights on and they work, it all made sense. Bob Vila would have been proud.</p>\n\n<p>The idea of getting all of this set up was because my sister was turning thirty on saturday and I needed to get the bar hooked up because we were having a party. Dave and I spent a good portion of friday night and saturday mourning trying to get the kegerator to flow right. Once all was finally working correctly, I had no idea what we did different, but it worked flawlessly. We had the dispenser in the wall and the correct amount of CO2 come party time.</p>\n\n<p>Once all was said and done, it  appeared everyone had a good time. The cops showed up because apparently they didn&rsquo;t like the idea that we were lighting off illegal fireworks that darrough brought over. Its probably a good thing I didn&rsquo;t talk to him, but from what I hear he was pretty cool. Regardless, I gotta have more parties like that one. Now that I think about it, my birthday is next week. Maybe thats too soon? Ahh, I&rsquo;m getting a keg anyway.</p>\n\n<p>When sunday came along, I was presented with some bad news. My basement reeks like beer and somehow I erased my entire itunes collection thats was on the mac mini. I was doing a remote desktop thing, so maybe that had something to do with. It really makes no sense and its times like this that I can&rsquo;t honestly say OSX is that superior of an operating system.</p>\n\n<p>In other news, the new <a href=\"http://www.punknews.org/bands/lagrecia\" title=\"lagrecia\">Lagrecia</a> (and apparently the only one they will release) came out today. I wasn&rsquo;t quick enough to the draw to get a free version, but I&rsquo;ll jam the stream and if it lives up, I will certainly purchase it. From the first couple of rounds, I&rsquo;m not sure if I&rsquo;m sold yet.</p>",
