        "body": "<p>So its official, I have gone two weeks without making a blog entry. Last week was memorial day weekend, I was busy, and it was rachel&rsquo;s birthday. Speaking of which, I am beginning to feel like a total ass that I didn&rsquo;t join her at the premier of sex and the city. Instead I am here listening and watching the <a href=\"http://twitlive.tv/\" title=\"http://twitlive.tv/\">live stream</a> of the latest <a href=\"http://twit.tv\" title=\"TWiT\">twit</a> installment and blogging away to you the reader. I also had to mow the lawn with my <a href=\"http://www.lowes.com/lowes/lkn?action=productDetail&amp;productId=227683-53393-26053&amp;lpage=none\" title=\"task force mower\">pseudo lawnmower</a>. I know I am keeping the earth healthy but the fact that <a href=\"http://www.lowes.com/lowes/lkn?action=productDetail&amp;productId=227683-53393-26053&amp;lpage=none\" title=\"task force mower\">this thing</a> doesn&rsquo;t cut a piece of grass over 5 inches leaves me kind of screwed.</p>\n\n<p>Regardless how busy I am on this sunday afternoon, the red wings won on yesterday and the possibility of winning the stanley cup tomorrow night are strong.  I have to play golf beforehand, but will be done by eight and its going to be on. As far as I am concerned, pittsburgh got lucky as hell last week with their only win. Their holding on for dear life and all I can say is &ldquo;good luck&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<p>I&rsquo;ve been trimming my beard after every round of the playoffs and its doesn&rsquo;t look any better than after the first. I also got new tires and am $200 dollars broker. But thats OK, I&rsquo;m a believer.</p>\n\n<p>LET&rsquo;s GO RED WINGS.</p>\n\n<p>Joe</p>",
