        "body": "<p>So I officially moved out of my <a href=\"http://www.peregrinetowers.com/res_122_lovell.htm\" title=\"lovell st\">current living quarters</a> into some place new. The suburbs of kalamazoo if you will. I guess if you could call it that. I am extremely disappointed that I am currently missing the last episode of <a href=\"http://www.hbo.com/thewire/\" title=\"the wire\">the wire</a>. Bag that, I am pissed off and rachel is hearing all about it. At least I didnt miss because I forgot that today was the day we spring head.</p>\n\n<p>Regardless I have a new place to live and a somewhat new outlook on life. I have a new lab which means a new place to create music. A new place to create web applications. A new place to create&hellip;&hellip;its endless. I have to say that I am a little bummed I have to move. I had a bunch of good memories of this place.</p>\n\n<p>I got locked out twice. Once I had to scale the side of the building in the middle of winter using rachel as boost to get in. Another I walked over to <a href=\"http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&amp;friendid=113890011\" title=\"harveys\">harveys</a>, played pinball and drank beer until I received phone call.  I had few gatherings there. None were real good until the spring came and we fired up the drums at seven in the mourning to hear against the east wall of the state theater. I remember hearing the <a href=\"http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&amp;friendID=113381995\" title=\"pbr\">poor bastards revolt</a> and some young hipsters paying rock music in the street around the corner, then walking down the street to see them.Many more good time, I just cannot take the space hear. Walking to the park is awesome. Hearing the park even awesomer. Here&rsquo;s to 2008, bring me something good.</p>\n\n<p>In other news, I just bought the mistic pizza / say anything dvd combination and plan on watching it. Of course after I finish the chapelle show season 2.</p>",
