        "body": "<p>I really dont know WHAT to say about this:</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://online.wsj.com/article/SB120485166974418241.html?mod=hpp_us_inside_today\" title=\"romeo\">http://online.wsj.com/article/SB120485166974418241.html?mod=hpp_us_inside_today</a></p>\n\n<p>How about holy shit?</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://joef.org/wp-content/themes/couch/images/lilromeo.jpg\" alt=\"lil romeo\" style=\"float: right; margin: 5px;\"/></p>\n\n<p>In the  bathroom today at work I was skimming through the community wall street journal and saw <a href=\"http://online.wsj.com/article/SB120485166974418241.html?mod=hpp_us_inside_today\" title=\"romeo\">this article</a>. Actually, you really couldn&rsquo;t missed it because it was on the front page of the Personal Journal section. Apparently lil&rsquo; romeo got a full ride scholorship to USC for basketball because he chummed up with some kid from Compton and his dad is Master P. Not only is this bullshit being that he&rsquo;s not that good at basketball but the fact that this comes with a $44,000 price tag that is totally comped. I am sure this sort of thing happens all the time, but I just hope this story gets the exploitation it deserves. The visual chart was the funniest part to me. Oh, and this quote:</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;We may have more 11- to 17-year-old girls in the stands than we&rsquo;ve had in the past&hellip;&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>And what exactly does lil&rsquo; romeo have to say about all of this?</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;my game will speak for itself.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>Let&rsquo;s hope so romeo. We&rsquo;re routing for you!</p>\n\n<p>In other news, I hope this dude head explodes - <a href=\"http://www.sajalkayan.com/facebook-founder-is-the-worlds-youngest-billionaire.html\" title=\"mark zuckerburg\">http://www.sajalkayan.com/facebook-founder-is-the-worlds-youngest-billionaire.html</a></p>",
