        "title": "black history month 2008",
        "body": "<p>So another black history month is upon us and I almost past it without acknowledgment. This year I wanted to pay homage to a great african american many seem to over look. Thats right, the one and only <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jim_Kelly_(martial_artist)\" title=\"jim kelly\">Mr. Jim Kelly</a>. Not to be confused with the quarterback,  Jim excelled in dojos across america as a professional martial artist. His craft was so polished even hollywood came calling. Staring in many films throughout the seventies, Jim hit the height of his career kung fuing along side the late great <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bruce_Lee\" title=\"bruce lee\">Bruce Lee</a>.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2186/2277953331_8bcf71dac1_m.jpg\" alt=\"blackbelt\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 5px\" height=\"162\" width=\"240\"/></p>\n\n<p>The first saw Jim in the great exploitation film <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Belt_Jones\" title=\"black belt jones\">Black Belt Jones</a>. Not only was this film action packed, but at twelve years old, surprisingly amusing to me.  The next time I saw him was in <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0070034/\" title=\"enter the dragon\">Enter the Dragon</a> a couple of years later. I never actually realized this was the same guy until about a month ago. Then when I thought about it, I asked myself how many black professional kung fuers could there be? Then I realized that <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kareem_Abdul-Jabbar\" title=\"kareem\">Kareem Abdul-Jabar</a> was actually in a film with Bruce Lee. I suppose I have to watch more kung fu (or more black exploitation files, who knows.)</p>\n\n<p>Its too late this year, but I got a great idea for this month - better luck next. I gotta go, Pam Grier&rsquo;s on the L Word.</p>\n\n<p>Happy Black History month everyone.</p>\n\n<p>Joe</p>",
