        "title": "lets pray",
        "body": "<p>Holy christ these people on this wipe  swap show are religious. I cant honestly say that I would clean for jesus or that the kids constitution is the best way to raise a child, but who I am to judge. I just hope this chick dont grow up and marry someone as goonie as her father .</p>\n\n<p>I discovered this afternoon that my site just doesnt look completely correct with internet explorer. Actually it looks completely wrong, but thats what I get for not looking at it in IE before rolling it out.  Really only the header&rsquo;s goofy, but I am in the process of fixing it. I am hoping that no one is honestly using IE to surf the internet. But that happens. And if it does, <a href=\"http://getfirefox.com\" title=\"firefox\">think about changing lanes.</a></p>\n\n<p>In other news, I think I joined <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/thedimestoresaints\" title=\"the dime store saints\">a band</a>. Well, actually kind of start one. After the first rock session this week, I have a good feeling. Its going have soul and it rips. I hope I get some inspiration this weekend after attending  <a href=\"http://www.thelovedonesband.com/\" title=\"the loved ones\">the loved ones </a>show this weekend. Oh, and the <a href=\"http://www.gaslightanthem.com/\" title=\"the gaslight anthem.\">gaslight anthem</a> is playing as well (shit yeah !!). This new EP of theirs is  totally rad to my ears. My only complaint is that its only four songs  thus am afraid that I might get sick of it too quickly. I would have an opinion on the new loved ones, but the best buy and no other store in my neck of the woods carries it. I really dont want to make this digital transition but unfortunately its inevitable.</p>\n\n<p>joe</p>",
