        "title": "get stuff accomplished",
        "body": "<p>So, its official, I am hitched. Its not that different. It just feels good that everything is over with. Yet, at the same time, its a bit depressing. I was surrounded by a lot of friends and family for longer than I have in a while and then it was right back to work. Oh well, I have the fall to look forward to.</p>\n\n<p>I did come to the realization that I truely need to get my life organized. I have been using the <a href=\"http://www.uncalendar.com/\">the uncalendar</a> since college and has helped a bit to get my life in line, but not all the way. I figure with the combination of this and some digital tools I can really get down to business. I think i am going to take a page from the book of <a href=\"http://43folders.com\">merlin mann</a> and try out some life hacks. Maybe even read <a href=\"http://www.43folders.com/2004/09/08/getting-started-with-getting-things-done/\">a book</a> about it. But I dont see this happening. Yet, this kind of attitude is a perfect example of why the orginization in my life is the way it it. It time to take some steps.</p>\n\n<p>In other news, I went to the <a href=\"http://www.kalamazooirish.org/fest.php\">kalamazoo irish fest</a> last weekend and had a great time. Except when I tried to get on Jason&rsquo;s shoulders and fell into the flower bed and landed on my hand. I havent been able to move my figures very well, thus cant play the guitar. I really hope this wears off by sunday. I need to rock.</p>\n\n<p>joe</p>",
