        "title": "autumn is upon us",
        "body": "<p>Wow, one month, no entry, I feel like a fool. I&rsquo;ve been real busy this last month, unfortunately is was not in the lab. But after this weekend, thats all going to change. I got a lot in the works and its gonna be fun. The temperature is lowering in the lab because summer is ending and fall is almost here, so thats a relief.</p>\n\n<p>I finish the <a href=\"http://joef.org\" title=\"joe fearnley blog\">joef.org</a> <a href=\"http://m.joef.org\" title=\"joe fearnley mobile blog\">mobile version</a> about two days after my last post. As far as the user agent recognition goes, I cant really test it at this point. I sat on my phone last weekend and am waiting until after the wedding to get a new one.  When I mean sat on it, I mean I literally sat on the thing and broke the screen all to shit. It was in my back pocket and I somehow forgot about it. Maybe it was the the booze and strippers, but I beg to differ.</p>\n\n<p>So far as the things in the works. I have decided after the <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/seatfest\" title=\"sweat fest\">sweatfest</a> I am going to start a band. No, really this time. I got almost four songs written (no vocals yet) and am going to record them as soon as I complete them. I am going for a nineties melodic hardcore sound. Its gonna be sweet.</p>\n\n<p>Other than that, I have decided to turn the dell desktop into a server. The maverick was just not cutting it. Loud, slow, and using up a bunch of useless power. I am going for it this time. I will document the process. I currently am updating the portage tree, then to version 2007.0 of <a href=\"http://gentoo.org\" title=\"gentoo linux\">gentoo</a>.  I attempt to remove X11 and gnome from it. We&rsquo;ll see how that goes.</p>\n\n<p>The college housing application has got about no where. I pretty much gave up on it. It has potential. Maybe when I have some free time I will finish it. After last to speaking with jeff about it, it sounds like he wants to go into a search able map direction. I saw a <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Beginning-Google-Maps-Applications-Rails/dp/1590597877\" title=\"google apps application\">book</a> on developing google map apps with php and ajax. Maybe this can be my chance to finally dive into ajax. We&rsquo;ll see.</p>\n\n<p>joe</p>",
