        "title": "laber day",
        "body": "<p>Another week down and I am still alive. This is really something considering I had two bachelor parties in one week. My liver should took a beating this last week, but what’s new? I am also that much closer to getting hitched. Its a bit surreal sometimes, but we must forge ahead, leaving the past in the past.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/1271531788/\" title=\"Photo Sharing\"><img src=\"http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1020/1271531788_bad111ce32_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"192\" alt=\"IMAGE_135\"/></a></p>\n\n\t<p>Monday night was pretty dang gnarly. We got take a road trip in a van to a punk rock show and saw a couple of really sweet bands.  Rise against have come along way since seeing them a few years ago. They are like rock stars now with this giant show they put on. I guess with that kind of budget and hit singles, you gotta kind of expect that. I think one of the hight lights of the night was seeing smoke or fire. They have been on of my favorite bands these last couple of years. Lost my voice after watching them…story to tell. Comback kid was sweet and silverstien not so much. Ending the night at little darlings was just icing on the cake.</p>\n\n\t<p>Last saturday was a bit of a different story. Burgers, beers, chickin wings, a little golf, and a night ended a murphy lee’s couldnt have been a better formula for a good time. Though I am now broke and need a new phone, I wouldnt want to take it back. Like in the song that seemed to be the soundtrack to the week, I wouldn’t have changed anything for the world.</p>\n\n\t<p>joe</p>",
