        "title": "forecheck",
        "body": "<p>After another season of NHL down, I am not only dissapointed the red wings had to leave early, but anehiem won the cup. I guess it is far to say that detroit would have had a great shot in the finals, but who knows. When you are facing some one like daniel alfredson, you really can’t predict anything. I mean, not only being a god in some countries, he carried the senators on his back through the playoffs. HE had the mvp in his pocket but it not a whole lot of help from his teammates. And I just love how he shoots the puck at neidemeyer. It just shows that you can be a hard ass and be the top producer in the nhl playoffs.</p>\n\n\t<p>I just have to think that canadians are throwing rocks right now. Who would of thought a team from south california would be the stanley cup champions? Not me. I guess that things are chaniging but I dont know for the better or the worse. One thing that makes me want to vomit at moments is when nbc pans to that idiot named pierre that talks in the space between the benches. I always hope the guy catches a puck to the eye so we dont have to listen to his halfass game analasys or interviews;</p>\n\n\t<p>Oh, and I just realized that scott and rob neidermyer are brothers. I actually that the two were the same person. No wonder I always had them mixed up.</p>\n\n<p><strong>update:</strong> this really is not an update, I just want eveyone to know that I vaugely remeber writing this three weeks ago and am finally posting it.</p>\n\n\t<p>joe</p>",
