        "title": "applicationville",
        "body": "<p>So now that I have proven to myself that I can configure a linux server, I decided it was time to move on with my projects. Actually the whole server thing feel a bit like a waste because its not real accessible because I am trying to conserve energy cost and never have it on. Anyway, next stop, web applicationville. After months of badgering, I have finally given in to jeff&rsquo;s idea to create a college housing site. I jumped on this thing for two reasons. First, I am finding myself stoked to design another website. Second, after lending a hand with dave&rsquo;s homework, I found an urge to sharpen up my php skills. Try somethings I never have with php before and hopefully learn how to develop with it really well.</p>\n\n<p>My vision for this site is fairly simple. I figure it will contain two major segments. One being a search able database of housing around college campuses. It should as accommodating as possible for the end user. All the necessary filtering and navigation options and even offer things like suggestions to certain searches. The next segment would be a application for landlords. This landlord, or house administrator, could log on to the site and maintain a list of houses he or she has available. Essentially it would be a database maintained by the landlord that search able by the end user (or college student).</p>\n\n<p>Is this thing going to have any appeal or even be marketable? Who knows,Â  I dont really care. I just feel the need to get my hands dirty. Assuming the wire is not on television at the moment.</p>\n\n<p>Joe</p>",
