        "title": "how to pray",
        "body": "<p>The summer has been coming to quite the close. Saw <a href=\"http://www.strikeanywhere.org\">Strike Anywhere</a> last week totally rock the house in east lansing. That singer is a lot shorter in person. But he really makes up for it in his voice. All in all, its always great to see one of your favorite bands&rsquo; skills in action.</p>\n\n<p>I have been watching movies lately, especially documentories. I watched <a href=\"http://www.unaff.org/2001/f-soldiers.html\">this one</a> last week about anti-abortion extremists. Man, these people have lost it. This one dude named <a href=\"http://www.armyofgod.com\">paul hill</a> claimed god told him to murder an abortion doctor. Click on his name to see what these crazy people are all about.</p>\n\n<p>I also watched <a href=\"http://www.sho.com/site/schedules/product_page.do?seriesid=0&amp;episodeid=127640\">another one</a> about the blood gangs in South Central, LA. It was like one extreme to another. I found this one really intriguing for some reason. I have always got a kick out of the west coast gang life, but I guess this was the first time I have ever seen the real side of it. Pretty neat stuff.</p>\n\n<p>For the future, I am setting up shop in my basement. I am coining it <strong>jf labs</strong>, and plan to pursue projects down there. Everything from recording music to configuring web servers. The <a href=\"http://labs.joef.org\">site</a> is not up yet, but will be in a couple of weeks. It will be full of details about my trials and tribulations which if anyone is reading this probably dont care about. As for now, I discovered the whole area is flooded. I dont know if it was because of the rain or my dehumidifier broke, havent found the problem. But, if it was the rain, then <a href=\"http://labs.joef.org\">the lab</a> is in trouble.</p>\n\n<p>My first plan is to get this site out of beta. A paging system will do.</p>\n\n<p>joe</p>",
