        "body": "<p>So&hellip;.went to a killer show last weekend. I mean, look at the bill&hellip;you got&hellip;<a href=\"http://www.awilhelmscream.com\">the scream</a>&hellip;<a href=\"http://www.thelawrencearms.net\">the larry arms</a>&hellip;and <a href=\"http://www.lagwagon.com\">the wagon</a>. This was certainly one of the best shows I have ever seens and definately a highlight of my summer. <a href=\"http://www.lagwagon.com\">The wagon</a> played all the jams even <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HITFdN4D9Xg&amp;search=lagwagon\">move the car</a>, which is argueably my favorite lagwagon song ever. I didnt get to hear <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1fctLoYYuIU&amp;search=lagwagon\">bury the hatchet</a>, but I can always resort to <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/results?search=lagwagon&amp;search_type=search_videos&amp;search=Search\">youTube</a> for that one.</p>\n\n<p>So&hellip;I got a new laptop. Well new to me, but certainly not new to the technological world. It has all the specs I demanded and got quite a deal on it. So, I finally get to create the ultimate <a href=\"http://gentoo.org\">gentoo</a> machine, something that I have always wanted to do.</p>\n\n<p>In other news, I was in Burger King the other day and saw the most amazing thing. When I say amazing, I mean this in a disgusting way. Just when I think americas claim to fame (aka Fast Food Resturants) are becoming more health concious, they release a quadruple bacon cheeseburger. The Nutrition Facts posting just isnt enough king, OK.</p>\n\n<p>Then I think to myself, who in there right mind what want to eat one of these things? I then recall a time I was eating with <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/vanslamrock\">Eric Posthumous</a> and he special ordered a burger at the Station that wieghed a pound and a half and the waitress pointed this out to him. Then he eat the whole thing (with fries!!) Then I thought, oh yeah, <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/vanslamrock\">Eric Posthumous</a> might.</p>\n\n<p>joe</p>",
