        "title": "for the record",
        "body": "<p>First of all, for the record, the  <a href=\"http://www.dragonforce.com\">dragon force</a> show was extremely rad. I have never seen so much shredding in my life. Oh, and <a href=\"http://www.protestthehero\">protest the hero</a> was good as well. I wrote about the intersting experience Jason, Dan, and I had while there. You can read it on <a href=\"http://myspace.com/joefearnley\">myspace</a>.</p>\n\n<p>In other news, I have made some updates to my site. I incorperated a <a href=\"http://./search.php\">search</a> function and now users dont have to search the old fashioned way. I am still debating the keeping of the form no the index page, its doesnt look right, well see. I also added an  <a href=\"http://./rss/\">rss</a> feed to the site. To be honest, I dont know if the xml form is valid for a feed reader, but it looks good and that is all I really am concerned about at this point. Lastly, I added a <a href=\"http://./changelog.txt\">change log</a> to the site for users to view my development progress. I have kept no track of versioning up until this point (and still really dont because its all manual), so I started at 0.8.0. So I guess this site in still in its beta stage and that is so web 2.0. Does that make me hip to the web community? Who knows. I should put *beta* somewhere in the header to let everyone know.</p>\n\n<p>For the future, I have plans to add other rss feeds, including my <a href=\"http://./things.php\">things</a> (or interesting articles if you will), and a section of the current book(s) I am reading (yes I read sometimes). So well see, I might get this thing into production one day. Only time will tell.</p>\n\n<p>joe</p>",
