        "note_count": 0,
        "title": "super duper",
        "body": "<p>So last week I was in what most would call a predicament. After I was all hyped up on the mac mini I got, I just realized how much I didnt like the interface. It is wierd. The mouse moves funky and when I exit the terminal, the window doesnt close. I dont know, I just find these things to impead my computing experience. I was thinking its time to sell this thing….I have debts to pay off and as honestly, I can only use one computer at a time.</p>\n\n<p>Then a couple of things happened. First of all, the linux box is gone. Wasnt preparing for that one. I just got the wireless card working and was ready to begin configuring the best gentoo system ever. I tell you what, you tried to be nice and …. anyway. So then I read this article about how you can use your mac mini as a pre-production studio with a <a href=\"http://www.griffintechnology.com/products/imic2/\">$40 piece of hardware</a>. I got to thinking about how I dont play my guitar that much anymore and how fun it was to be in a band. So, I took the mini downstairs, made a purchase from <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com\">amazon</a>, set up a workspace, and now I am making music.</p>\n\n<p>At this point I have only played with it a couple of time. I recorded one guitar part with <a href=\"http://www.apple.com/ilife/garageband/\">GarageBand</a> built-in modern rock guitar effect and it didnt sound too bad. I will update the progress, if I acheive any.</p>\n\n<p>joe</p>",
