        "title": "black history month",
        "body": "<p>I managed to scramble through this entire month without acknowledging one of my favorite cultures. I dont watch very much TV, but it I really havent seem that much about Black History Month. I have no theories on why this is and frankly dont want to get in the habit of caring. Yet this is difficult because over the past year I have met some really great people. Some of them have even become part of my family and for this I am thankful.</p>\n\n<p>I watched one film in particular in january that made think a bit. I want to pay omage to one inidividual that I think we can all learn from . Young, black, and dont give a f**k&hellip;.America&rsquo;s worst nightmare&hellip;my dog&hellip;your dog&hellip;old dog.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/couch/images/old_dog_mod.jpg\" alt=\"olddog\" height=\"192\" width=\"280\"/></p>\n\n<p>So, for what it is worth, happy Black History Month everyone! Let the admired know.</p>\n\n<p>joe</p>",
