                "content_raw": "<p>I read the most <a href=\"http://blogcritics.org/archives/2006/01/13/213613.php\"> interesting article</a> a few weeks back. I even read it 2 more times since, including once today. I have officially been made aware that I am not the only person that has to deal with this. I have purchased a <a href=\"http://www.thinkgeek.com/tshirts/frustrations/388b/\"> new t-shirt</a> and plan on wearing it often.</p>\n<p>I have also decided to change the name of my occupation when I tell people. My professional title is now software engineer, which I dont really know if I can consider myself one, but if someone actually proves to me that I am not one, then that person can refer to my occupation as computer programmer.</p>\n<p>Like the author mentions in the article, I neither do not fully trust computers. If I have any significant data on my computer, I back it up so if something were to go ary, it wont take me long to reinstall the operating system (unless of course I am installing gentoo). Even though the process can be irritating, it is worth it to me.</p>\n<p>So the next time you cant connect to the internet, realize this is a networking issue and I learned nothing about this topic in school other than using the ssh terminal and a web browser, so to be completely honest, odds are <em>I dont know</em>. If I were to attempt to solve your problem, you <em>can</em> do what I would do since I have no more knowledge than you do (at least on this subject). Before the faintest thought of the combination of *joe* and *computer* pop into your head, go to <a href=\"http://www.google.com\">google</a> and type in your problem or error message. Odds are, you are probably not the first person this has happened to, and there is a solution. </p>\n<p>But I have a hard time saying no to people, so I will probably fake like I do know and try to help.</p>\n<p>happy v-day</p>\n<p>joe</p>",
