        "body": "<p>I recieved my <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/joefearnley/91270520/\">mac mini</a> in the mail the other day. I truely want to say that I like it, but it certainly is taking some getting used to. I suppose I am not saying that I dont like it, but the interface is a bit different and this single-button mouse world is putting up its dukes up to my double-button mouse world, that for sure. If worse comes to worse, I can always revert, inputs are quite compatable.</p>\n\t<p>I do like the unix-like terminal and installing “amp” was a snap. I can now ssh with out opening a seperate application and the visual aspect of <span class=\"caps\">OSX</span> is pretty neat. Yet, how much more similar the <a href=\"http://www.gnome.org\">linux desktops</a> are to windows surprised me.</p>\n\t<p>So in my quest to push <a href=\"http://www.microsoft.com\">windows</a> away, I will continue to adjust. Anyone interested in buying a <a href=\"http://./dell.php\">dell</a> at a cheap price, let me know </p>\n\t<p>joe</p>",
