        "body": "<p>Hello to those who are visiting. First off, I would like to thank you for visiting the <a href=\"mailto:%20joe@joef.org\">joe fearnley</a> web place.. I started this site back in the summer time, working on it on and off. I have the initial design down but have a long way to go in the background of this bad oscar.</p>\t<p>The first thing would have to be integrating a blogging mechanism into this site. Though I have it almost completed, the backlash of internet security is the main drawback. I have looked into using systems like <a href=\"http://www.wordpress.org\">wordpress</a> and <a href=\"http://www.movabletype.org\">movable type</a>, but once I tried to figure out how to create my own style for something like this, it seems quicker just to build it myself. So as my foolishness gets the best of me, I find it more and more difficult the deeper I proceed into development. So maybe I will just say “screw it”, conform, and look back on how much time I wasted trying to <acronym title=\"Do It Myself\"><span class=\"caps\">DIM</span></acronym>.</p>\t<p>I suppose the next step would be to have comments for the blogs and a designated area for visitors to say what they would like.</p>",
